<comment type="function">
<text>Toxic peptide whose overexpression causes rapid cell killing and nucleoid condensation of the host cell (By similarity).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="induction">
<text>A type I toxin antitoxin (TA) system, where expression of the proteinaceous toxin is controlled by an antisense sRNA, in this case rdlB. Only a few of these TA systems have been mechanistically characterized; the mechanisms used to control expression of the toxin gene are not necessarily the same (Probable).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text>Belongs to the toxic peptide ldr family.</text>
</comment>
